CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 28, 1956, page 28, reads: "'Operation Big Feed' - Taking an active part in State Game Conservation program in the Bucktail Hunting and Fishing Club. Its members recently purchased 3,400 pounds of corn which it will distribute to deer in the mountains. Ready for their third annual feeding trip are, left to right, 'Al' Wilkins (in truck), Clifton Poinsette, A. J. Scott, L. pg. Newson, James Smith and Henry D. Williams. The club will hold its third annual game dinner Saturday night at the Court of Calanthe Hall, Centre Avenue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bucktail Hunting and Fishing Club, left to right: Clifton Poinsette, driver, 'Al' Wilkins, A. J. Scott, James Smith,Henry D. Williams, and L. P. Newson, gathered around truck with sign that reads "Bucktail Hunting & Fishing Club of Pittsburgh Annual Game Feeding Program at Port Allegheny Pennsylvania", parked in front of Handelman Sandwich Shop and their clubhouse shop front, street no. 2105, on a snowy day
